### =========================================================================
### PHASE 1: USER REGISTRATION (Create Clean Database Records)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Register an Admin Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "System Administrator", 
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### 2. Register a Passenger Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ahmad Passenger",
  "email": "passenger@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "passenger"
}

### 3. Register a Driver Account
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Captain Khaled",
  "email": "driver@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "driver"
}

### =========================================================================
### PHASE 2: LOGIN & GENERATE JWT TOKENS (Saves tokens into variables)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Login as Admin
# @name adminLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Admin Token
@adminToken = {{adminLogin.response.body.access_token}}

### -------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 2. Login as Passenger
# @name passengerLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "passenger@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Passenger Token
@passengerToken = {{passengerLogin.response.body.access_token}}

### -------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 3. Login as Driver
# @name driverLogin
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "driver@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Store Driver Token
@driverToken = {{driverLogin.response.body.access_token}}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 3: THE CORRECT FLOW (FULL RIDE LIFECYCLE)
### =========================================================================

### 1. Driver goes ONLINE (Must be online to receive trips)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/users/driver-status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "status": "online"
}

### 2. Passenger Requests a Trip
POST http://localhost:3000/trips
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

{
  "startLocation": "Al-Hashimi Al-Shamali",
  "endLocation": "Petra Ride"
}

### 3. Driver checks for Available Trips
GET http://localhost:3000/trips/available
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

### 4. Driver ACCEPTS the Trip (Assuming Trip ID is 1)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

### 5. Driver STARTS the Trip
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1/start
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

### 6. Driver COMPLETES the Trip (Sets the final price)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1/complete
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "price": 12.50
}

### 7. Passenger Leaves a Rating
POST http://localhost:3000/ratings
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

{
  "tripId": 1,
  "stars": 5,
  "comment": "Excellent service and smooth ride!"
}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 4: SECURITY & ROLE TESTING (Testing to get 403 Forbidden / 400 Bad Request)
### =========================================================================

### SECURITY TEST A: Driver tries to request a trip (Should get 403 Forbidden)
POST http://localhost:3000/trips
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "startLocation": "Downtown",
  "endLocation": "Amman Mall"
}

### SECURITY TEST B: Passenger tries to accept a trip (Should get 403 Forbidden)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/1/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{passengerToken}}

### SECURITY TEST C: Driver tries to accept a trip while offline (Change status to offline first)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/users/driver-status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}

{
  "status": "offline"
}

### Now try to accept trip 2 (Should get 400 Bad Request)
PATCH http://localhost:3000/trips/2/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{driverToken}}


### =========================================================================
### PHASE 5: ADMIN MANAGEMENT & REPORTING
### =========================================================================

### Get All Registered Users
GET http://localhost:3000/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get All Active Drivers Only
GET http://localhost:3000/users/drivers
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Get System Trip History
GET http://localhost:3000/trips
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}